proposed that the dispersal of the Neotropical entomofauna towards the Mexican Plateau began prior to the elevation of this region, during the upper Cretaceous and early Eocene. This entomofauna evolved into endemic lineages of the southern United States of America, northern Mexico, the Balsas basin and the highlands of Chiapas and Guatemala (

